## Flow description

This flow shows how to use function modules. Function modules are the [npm modules](https://www.npmjs.com/) that extend the capabilites of function node. They don't add nodes to the Node-RED palette. They can be imported and used only in function nodes.

## How to use function modules
1. First you need to make sure that the module you want to import is available for your offer. Go to **Palette > Function** and search for the module you need. If you cannot find it, you can submit a request for adding a new module to the offer.
![function modules tab](data:image/png;base64,)

2. To install and import a function module to your Node-RED just add a **function node**, double click on it and go to **Setup** tab. Then add the module by its npm name e.g. [cowsay](https://www.npmjs.com/package/cowsay). Optionally you can change the imported variable name under *Import as*.
![importing a function module](data:image/png;base64,)

3. As soon as you click the *Save* button, Node-RED will install the module (if it hasn't already been installed). 

4. After a while you are able to use the imported module.
